I just returned from a fantastic weekend, a new beginning for me personally and for my family.  If there is anything we can take from this site it is that there are new beginnings after endings.  There will be another site to write upon, another day will bring another sunrise, and another point of view to be considered.  <br><br>
To those whose may come by this site when it is &quot;read-only,&quot; I ask that you begin the strings from their beginnnings, and not in the middle.  To understand the discussions, arguments, stories and poems, you really have to follow the flow of each string.  They are different, and their eb and flow is not regular, but it does occur.  Just as reading a good book is best accomplished beginning to end, these discussions are best read beginning to end.  Some of the discussions went on simultaniously on different strings, and some entries refer to the other ones.  <br><br>
To all, I wish you the best of new beginnings.
<p><code>-- John C. Ratliff  (New Beginnings) </code><p>


